      <h2>The Bottom Line</h2>

      <p>Declining open rates are a symptom, not a disease. The disease is almost always an infrastructure problem&mdash;domain reputation decay, excessive sending volume, DNS authentication failures, or list quality deterioration. Subject line optimization, while valuable, is the correct response in only 8% of cases. Fix the infrastructure first, and open rates recover. Ignore the infrastructure and optimize subject lines, and you will burn time tweaking copy while your emails continue landing in spam.</p>

